value.value: 上腕リンパ節の欠如
absence of the lymph nodes located along the brachial vein that receive drainage from most of the free upper limb and send efferent vessels to the central axillary lymph nodes
上腕リンパ節の矮小化
reduced size of the lymph nodes located along the brachial vein that receive drainage from most of the free upper limb and send efferent vessels to the central axillary lymph nodes
腋窩リンパ節の欠如
absence of the lymph nodes located around the axillary vein that receive lymphatic drainage from the upper or forelimb, scapular region and pectoral region
腋窩リンパ節の肥大
increased size of the lymph nodes located around the axillary vein that receive lymphatic drainage from the upper or forelimb, scapular region and pectoral region
腋窩リンパ節の矮小化
reduced size of the lymph nodes located around the axillary vein that receive lymphatic drainage from the upper or forelimb, scapular region and pectoral region
頸部リンパ節の欠如
absence of the lymph nodes normally found near the neck and shoulders
膝窩リンパ節の欠如
absence of the lymph nodes which drain the legs
膝窩リンパ節の肥大
increased size of the lymph nodes which drain the legs
膝窩リンパ節の矮小化
reduced size of the lymph nodes which drain the legs
視蓋前野の形態異常

any structural anomaly of a narrow, transversely oriented rostral zone of the mesencephalic tectum, bounded caudally by the superior colliculus, rostrally by the habenular trigone, and laterally by the pulvinar thalami; the pretectal area contains several nuclei that receive fibers from the optic tract; it has bilateral efferent connections with the Edinger-Westphal nucleus of the oculomotor nuclear complex by way of which it mediates the pupillary light reflex
視蓋前野核の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the groups of neurons located between the thalamus and midbrain that receive binocular sensory input from retinal ganglion cells of the eyes and are responsible for maintaining the pupillary light reflex
視蓋前野オリーブ核の形態異常

any structural anomaly of one of several pretectal nuclei with direct input from the eye and the only one containing neurons whose rate of firing is linearly related to the intensity of light falling on the retina
腎尿細管上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the cellular avascular layer of the renal tubule luminar surfaces
腎の退行変性
a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of either or both of the two excretory organs that filter wastes (especially urea) from the blood and excrete them and water in urine
血液恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of various functions or chemical or protein composition of the blood
尿恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of the various chemical or protein components of the urine
尿毒症
an excess of urea, creatinine, and other nitrogenous end products of protein and amino acid metabolism in the blood; usually indicative of kidney dysfunction
結晶尿
excretion of crystalline material in the urine
膀胱の炎症
local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the urinary bladder
受精頻度の減少
the number of secondary oocytes each penetrated by a spermatozoon followed by fusion of the male and female pronuclei are fewer than expected
異常な過排卵
altered ability of a female to be induced to ovulate an expected number of ova after treatment with specific gonadotrophic hormones
胚着床の遅延
any lag in the normal time course necessary for the attachment of the blastocyst to the endometrium
休止状態の胚盤胞
blastocysts sometimes larger than normal in size, showing no development or mitotic activity as a result of delayed implantation
眼瞼の発生異常
aberrant formation of the skin folds covering the front of the eyeball
口蓋襞の形態異常

any structural anomaly in the series of transverse folds (ridges) of the mucosa located on the anterior third part of the secondary (hard) palate of most mammalian species; rugae are present on each side of the median palatal raphe and behind the incisive papillae, but their number and arrangement are species specific; together with the teeth and the tongue, rugae take part in mastication by helping to sense, hold and mash the food; rugae harbor various types of intraepithelial sensory structures (such as Merckel cells, corpuscular endings and free nerve endings), and play a sensory role when the food is pressed by the tongue against the hard palate
口蓋の発生異常
abnormal formation of the roof of the mouth in vertebrates formed anteriorly by a bony projection of the upper jaw (hard palate) and posteriorly by the fold of connective tissue (soft palate)
一次口蓋の発生異常

any anomaly in the formation of the part of the shelf separating the oral and nasal cavities that is formed during early embryonic development from the medial nasal processes which derive from the frontonasal process; these merge with each other and with the bilateral maxillary processes to form the upper lip and the primary palate
二次口蓋の発生異常

any anomaly in the formation of the part of the palate that is formed during embryonic development when palatal projections from the inner part of the maxillary processes emerge, extend and elevate into a horizontal position above the tongue
絨毛尿膜の癒合遅延
late onset of the initiation and/or completion of the formation of a highly vascularized extra-embryonic fetal membrane by fusion of the chorion and allantois
絨毛尿膜の癒合不全
failure to initiate and/or complete the formation of a highly vascularized extra-embryonic fetal membrane by fusion of the chorion and allantois
胎盤アポトーシスの増加
increase in the number of cells of the placenta undergoing programmed cell death
細い溝のある毛皮
hair or fur characterized by transverse, usually parallel, markings due to an anomaly in hair color, texture, or growth
網膜の新血管新生誘導の異常
any anomaly in the response to conditions which induce the pathological growth of vessels into the retina
異常妊娠
any anomaly in the process of maintaining a developing embryo or fetus within the female body from conception to birth
子宮の胚受容能異常
any alteration in the time sensitive process of uterine differentiation that occurs in response to implantation competent blastocysts and precedes and is necessary for embryo implantation
子宮-胚軸の異常
any anomaly in the process whereby the implantation chamber orients in the uterus in response to decidual growth to insure correct alignment of the embryo to the uterus
管腔閉鎖異常
an anomaly in the degree to which (for each species) the uterine epithelium closes over and makes contact with, and secures an implanting blastocyst
胚対位の異常
any anomaly that prevents the initial positioning of the blastocyst trophoblast and uterine luminal epithelium causing the blastocyst to fail to orientate correctly along the uterine wall
胚付着の異常
any anomaly in the process whereby the blastocyst anchors to the uterine luminal epithelium and cannot be dislodged by flushing
胚侵入の異常
any anomaly in the process that enables the embryo to establish connection to the uterine luminal epithelium
子宮外妊娠
a fertilized egg attaches and begins development in a location other than in the inner lining of the uterus, most commonly in the Fallopian tube
着床後子宮環境の異常
failure of the uterus to undergo the changes necessary to support pregnancy following implantation of the embryo
子宮新血管新生異常
any anomaly in vascular permeability and blood vessel development that normally occurs in the uterus to support embryonic growth during pregnancy
子宮の生理異常
any functional anomaly of the female muscular organ of gestation in which the developing embryo or fetus is nourished until birth
出生時体重異常
anomaly in average weight at birth compared to controls
出生時体重の増加
increase in average weight at birth compared to controls
出生時体重の減少
reduction in average weight at birth compared to controls
正常角化
thickening of the stratum corneum of the epidermis (hyperkeratosis) with non-nucleated keratinocytes retained in this layer
止血異常
any anomaly in the spontaneous arrest of bleeding from vessels carrying blood under pressure or the arrest of circulation to an organ or part

label.value: abnormal spinal cord dorsal column morphology

value.value: 脊髄後柱の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal spinal cord dorsal column morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the wedge-shaped fiber bundle of white matter in the dorsomedial side of the spinal cord that is made up of the fasciculus gracilis and fasciculus cuneatus; it is part of the ascending posterior column-medial lemniscus pathway that is important for well-localized fine touch and conscious proprioception

definition.value: Note that the synonym posterior column may refer to either the grey matter dorsal horn or the white matter dorsal column in the spinal cord.
